description:
The main responsibility of the Security Systems Analyst is to support the efficient operation of the physical security systems technologies within the APAC region led by the Security Systems Supervisor and its operating within the Security Operations Centre . These technologies include, Electronic Access Control, Video Surveillance Systems, intrusion detection systems, communication systems and other risk-based technologies or solutions.

Primary activities include:

Ensures that routine maintenance undertaken in the APEC region maintains the systems integrity & reliability of its connectivity to the SCC by acting as 1st line support.

Reactively troubleshoots and supervises the remediation of any problems identified with any hardware or software within the APAC security portfolio either internally and via approved contracted companies where required.

Responsible for auditing the documentation and administration of the system ensuring alignment of all configuration, drawings... programming to the company systems standards for the purpose of management, global/regional data compliance and audits.

Provides end user training to SOC operators to efficiently utilise the system to monitor the APAC portfolio

Main responsibilities

Projects Works

o Commissions any system changes completed by approved third party contractors

o Programmes system configuration in accordance with documentation governed by the TWDC minimum security standards, target operating model, data protection requirements and local legislation

o Responsible for ensuring on-boarding to the SCC in an effective manner

o Support technical and application integrations across the APAC territory

Audit & Compliance

o Regularly tests and validates system effectiveness in its detection and monitoring capabilities

o Validates and updates where required site documentation detailing changes, schematics, configuration and installed assets.

o Ensures minimal nuisance systems alarms

o Confirms with IT department necessary storage, LAN & WAN capacity for operational effectiveness and redundancy capability

Service Management

o Manages GA case load received from multiple sources and locations and monitors time to resolution

o Scheduling of resources to minimise disruption to TWDC business.

o Oversees any reactive maintenance to be conducted as required in accordance with procedures set by TWDC.

o Monitors service performance against respective Service Level Agreements

o Ensures resources comply with necessary procedures and requirements of sites to complete remediation works.

o Validates resolutions of third party in accordance with TWDC standards and contractual requirements

o Ensure, in cooperation with the approved contracted companies, that sufficient spares are on hand throughout the region, to allow for continued operation of systems should an equipment failure occur;

People Management

o Daily management of contacting companies and internal stakeholders involved with systems;

o Have a full understanding of the functions covered at all sites including areas such as Security, CCTV, Reception and systems Support;

o Ensure adequate skill sets of all security staff to efficiently identify faults locally or virtually within the system

System Innovation

o Respond to changes in the external environment including legislation, technology and trends.

Operations Management

o Report on a daily basis with management to ensure effective communication of all systems matters to ensure the delivery of a high standard professional security service;

o Ensure all staff are trained to carry out their systems duties in accordance with procedures and policies;

o Work in partnership to raise the profile of security and fire prevention by attending meetings with service partners;

o Investigate incidents and prepare responses in accordance with policies and procedures;

o Understand drivers behind systems failures and to take steps to minimise losses.

Other Duties

o Be aware of policy and procedures owned and changed from time to time by APAC;

o Be aware of policy and procedures owned and changed from time to time by the client.

Any additional reasonable duties requested by operational management (APAC Contract Manager, APAC Technical Manager, APAC Security System Supervisor, TWDC Security Systems Senior Manager APAC).

Other duties and responsibilities

Work in accordance with:

o Security & Risk Solutions(SRS) policies, site procedures and training provided

o Customer policies

Carry out any other reasonable request as required by your Line Manager or the Customer.

Health and Safety responsibilities

Ensure work is carried out in accordance with site/department procedures and training provided.

Comply with the Health and Safety Policy, procedures and protocols at all times;

Ensure you have received the required training prior to commencing works;

Ensure that you are working in accordance with the safe system of works, as briefed by your Line Manager;

Ensure that you are fit for work prior to reporting for duty each day;

Report any health and safety concerns to your line manager;

Once Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) has been issued ensure that you keep it serviceable at all times and report any defects to your line manager;

Always ensure while at work you are wearing the correct PPE;

If you are operating machinery/plant/vehicles you must operate safely in accordance with the instruction and training provided;

Set a good example at all times;

Job specific

o Reporting immediately to the Contract Manager any action or inaction which compromises safety;

o Maintain a healthy and safe place of work, ensuring all posts are in a clean and tidy condition at all times;

o Report missing, damaged or unserviceable equipment to the Contract Manager;

o Co-operate with APAC and the client so that the company can carry out its statutory duty under Health & Safety policies and all relevant statutory provisions;

o Not intentionally or recklessly interfere with or misuse any property, equipment IT hardware or systems in the interest of Health & Safety and Welfare.

Required skills & Experience

Essential

Ability to meet all vetting requirements;

Background in Security Systems Management;

Working knowledge in providing security solutions;

Effective interpersonal & communication skills;

Experience of issue and conflict resolution;

Ability to work under own initiative, making decisions to benefit APAC and client;

Experience with raising work orders;

Competent on Microsoft Word/Excel/Outlook/PowerPoint;

Experience and good working knowledge of the following:

o Computer Networking and IT systems administration;

o Video Surveillance (FLIR/Genetec);

o Access control (Lenel, Lobby works, Galaxy);

o Reporting software (Global Aware);

o Mass notification systems (TRIS, ANVIL, 360, EVERBRIDGE).

o Control room SOP’s

Demonstrate the ability to think and act quickly in emergencies or under pressure;

Have an ability to deliver succinct and clear verbal and written reports where necessary;

Maintain a high standard of personal presentation;

Demonstrate reliability including the ability to deliver high standards of both punctuality and attendance in order to ensure team effectiveness and availability;

Able to demonstrate an ability to work as part of a team;

Able to deal calmly and confidently with all demands from the public;

An understanding of the principles of equality and diversity in relation to visitors’ needs;

An interest in and commitment to the work of SRS for its clients.

Desirable

Understanding of the International Standards in IT Security;

Experience with software such as CABS, CONDECO, CARDEX.

AutoCAD, draughtsman

Qualifications & Licences

Essential

Certification for Lenel, FLIR, Genetec etc.

Desirable

Systems Certification Licenses

First Aid at Work certificate

